
=Discussion=

Via openhardware.org:

"It is strongly recommended that you use the [http://wiki.openhardware.org/Recommended_Licenses Recommended Licenses] rather than the licenses on this list. The Recommended Licenses have been chosen to provide a minimal set of licenses, which are all compatible with each other, and which thus reduce the legal load upon the entire community. When you choose a license that isn't on the recommended list, you increase the legal load to developers and users unnecessarily.

The Certified License list has not been set yet. This list will be developed according to the [http://wiki.openhardware.org/Project:Certified_Open_Hardware_License_Approval_Process Certified Open Hardware License Approval Process].

Note that [http://wiki.openhardware.org/Hardware_Isn%27t_Generally_Copyrightable Hardware Isn't Generally Copyrightable]. Thus, there are severe limitations upon the enforcement of the licenses of hardware designs that do not exist for licenses applied to software."
(http://wiki.openhardware.org/Certified_Licenses)


